## Parent Epic
charmed_rust-idi: Add Syntax Highlighting to Glamour

## Objective
Create a robust mapping layer that converts syntect's Style (designed for GUI editors) to lipgloss's Style (designed for terminal rendering), preserving colors and text attributes.

## Detailed Requirements

### 1. Core Mapping Function
```rust
use syntect::highlighting::{Style as SynStyle, FontStyle as SynFontStyle};
use lipgloss::Style;

/// Convert syntect highlighting style to lipgloss terminal style
pub fn syntect_to_lipgloss(syn_style: SynStyle) -> Style {
    let mut style = Style::new();

    // Map foreground color
    let fg = syn_style.foreground;
    style = style.foreground(lipgloss::Color::rgb(fg.r, fg.g, fg.b));

    // Map background color (if not transparent)
    let bg = syn_style.background;
    if bg.a > 0 {
        style = style.background(lipgloss::Color::rgb(bg.r, bg.g, bg.b));
    }

    // Map font styles
    let font = syn_style.font_style;
    if font.contains(SynFontStyle::BOLD) {
        style = style.bold(true);
    }
    if font.contains(SynFontStyle::ITALIC) {
        style = style.italic(true);
    }
    if font.contains(SynFontStyle::UNDERLINE) {
        style = style.underline(true);
    }

    style
}
```

### 2. Theme Wrapper
```rust
use syntect::highlighting::{Theme, ThemeSet};

/// Wrapper for syntect themes with terminal-appropriate defaults
