## Acceptance Criteria

1. **Property Coverage**: Tests cover all parsing scenarios:
   - [ ] Single byte keys (ASCII, control chars)
   - [ ] Multi-byte UTF-8 characters
   - [ ] Escape sequences (CSI, SS3, OSC)
   - [ ] Function keys and special keys
   - [ ] Modified key combinations
   - [ ] Partial/incomplete sequences
   - [ ] Invalid/malformed input

2. **Invariant Verification**:
   - [ ] Parser never panics on any input
   - [ ] Consumed bytes never exceeds input length
   - [ ] Parsing is deterministic
   - [ ] Empty input handling is consistent

3. **Edge Case Coverage**:
   - [ ] Boundary values (0x00, 0x7F, 0xFF)
   - [ ] Maximum sequence lengths
   - [ ] Unicode edge cases (surrogates, overlong)

4. **Test Configuration**:
   - [ ] Appropriate case counts for CI (1000+)
   - [ ] Shrinking enabled for failure diagnosis
   - [ ] Reproducible with seed

